How to install igestis-roundcube
================================

From Debian/Ubuntu (apt-get)
----------------------------

Under Debian Squeeze add the Backports repository into /etc/apt/sources.list :

	deb http://backports.debian.org/debian-backports squeeze-backports main

Install Dovecot with sieve and imap support :

	apt-get install -t squeeze-backports dovecot-sieve dovecot-managesieved dovecot-imapd

Then install igestis-roundcube :

	apt-get install igestis-roundcube

Configure dovecot
-----------------

If you need the autologin , enable clear authentication 
by creating a file in /etc/dovecot/local.conf. Also, 
activate sieve and managesieved plugins in dovecot :

	mail_location = maildir:~/.Maildir
	disable_plaintext_auth = no

	service managesieve-login {
	  inet_listener sieve {
		port = 4190
	  }
	}

	protocol lda {
	  mail_plugins = $mail_plugins sieve
	}


Configure Postfix
-----------------

Specify to postfix that you want to use dovecot as lda and restart postfix :

	postconf -e "mailbox_command = /usr/lib/dovecot/deliver"

Users profile cleanup
---------------------

Don't forgot to remove the following files in the users folder if
applicable (check the content to see if there is useful information) :

	.fetchmailrc
	.procmailrc
	.procmail-roundcube
	.procmail-vacation
	.procmail-log


Configure Cyrus
---------------

You can configure to use Cyrus as well.
